</article><article class="clearfix full-article has-hero-image  time_article " id="article-3599505" data-article="3599505" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
  <header class="article-header">
    
    <section class="tags ">
  		  <a class="brand-tag brand-time-tag" href="http://time.com/" data-bypass="true">TIME</a>


            <a class="section-tag" itemprop="articleSection" href="http://time.com/business/" data-event="section-business">Business</a>

            <a class="topic-tag" itemprop="articleSection" href="http://time.com/tag/technology-media/" data-event="tag-technology-media" data-bypass="true">Technology &amp; Media</a>

      </section>
    <h2 class="article-title" itemprop="headline">A TV Network Should Buy Aereo. Here&#8217;s Why.</h2>
  <div class="article-sub-headline">
    <div class="article-meta">

        <ul class="article-authors">
            <li class="article-author ">
              <span class="byline"><a itemprop="author" href="http://time.com/author/alex-fitzpatrick/">Alex Fitzpatrick</a></span>
              <a class="author-twitter" target="_blank" href="https://twitter.com/alexjamesfitz">@alexjamesfitz</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <time class="publish-date" itemprop="datePublished" datetime="2014-11-21 11:52:36" pubdate>Nov. 21, 2014</time>
      
    </div>
    <div class="social-links">
      <a class="expand-share" href="javascript:void 0;" data-event="exp-micro" title="Click to view article share options">SHARE</a>
    <span class="social-links-tooltip">
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail" href="mailto:?subject=A%20TV%20Network%20Should%20Buy%20Aereo.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why.%20%7C%20TIME&body=A%20TV%20Network%20Should%20Buy%20Aereo.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why.%0A%0AIt%20would%20help%20them%20compete%20against%20Netflix%20and%20HBO%20Go%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F" data-event="email" title="Click to Email this article"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F" data-event="fb-share" title="Click to post this article to Facebook"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup" href="#" data-href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f6ox&text=Why%20a%20TV%20network%20should%20buy%20Aereo&via=TIMEBusiness" data-event="tweet" title="Click to Tweet this article"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-gplus social-link-gplus popup" href="https://plus.google.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F" data-event="google+" title="Click to post this article to Google+"></a>
    	<a class="time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup" href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F&title=A+TV+Network+Should+Buy+Aereo.+Here%E2%80%99s+Why." data-event="linkedin" title="Click to post this article to LinkedIn"></a>
    	
    </span>    </div>
  </div>  </header>  <section class="article-body" itemprop="articleBody">
    
    <figure class="landscape">
      <img src="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/aereo-buy.jpg?w=280" itemprop="image" alt="Supreme Court Hears Case Pinning Startup Internet TV Company Aereo Against Major Broadcast Networks" srcset="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/aereo-buy.jpg?w=1100 800w, http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/aereo-buy.jpg?w=1100 800w 2x"/>
      <figcaption class="image-caption">
        <span class="caption">In this photo illustration, Aereo.com, a web service that provides television shows online, is shown on an iPhone 4S on April 22, 2014 in New York City.</span>
        <span class="credit">Andrew Burton&mdash;Getty Images</span>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>
	<h2 class="article-excerpt" itemprop="alternativeHeadline">It would help them compete against Netflix and HBO Go</h2>
    <aside class="right-rail-module rr-related" data-name="rr-related"><div class="read-more-inline related"><a href="http://time.com/3599366/tv-streaming-startup-aereo-files-for-bankruptcy/" class="read-more-article" format-article data-event="rr-related"><img src="http://timedotcom.files.wordpress.com/2014/06/451262986.jpg?w=560&#038;h=374&#038;crop=1" alt="Supreme Court Rules Aereo Violates Copyrights" title="Aereo CEO Chet Kanojia holds one of the company&#039;s small antenna, May 22, 2014. "><h6 class="read-more-list-h">More</h6><h3 class="read-more-inline-title">TV-Streaming Startup Aereo Files for Bankruptcy</h3></a><a href="http://time.com/3566810/aereo-layoffs/" class="read-more-article" format-article data-event="rr-related"><h3 class="read-more-inline-title">Embattled TV Startup Aereo Is Laying Off Staff in NYC and Boston</h3></a><a href="http://time.com/3071126/aereo-court-bleeding-to-death/" class="read-more-article" format-video data-event="rr-related"><h3 class="read-more-inline-title">Aereo to Court: We&#8217;re &#8216;Bleeding to Death&#8217;</h3></a></div></aside><p>Aereo, an ambitious startup that aimed to stream live broadcast television to subscribers for a small monthly fee, <a href="http://time.com/3599366/tv-streaming-startup-aereo-files-for-bankruptcy/" target="_blank">filed for bankruptcy</a> Friday, months after a <a href="http://time.com/2923201/aereo-supreme-court-cord-cutters/" target="_blank">devastating loss</a> at the Supreme Court. But it doesn&#8217;t have to end this way.</p>
<aside class="right-rail-module rr-partner" data-name="rr-partner"><div class="read-more-list"><h6 class="read-more-list-h">More</h6><a href="http://time.com/3597304/amazon-washington-post-kindle/" class="read-more-list-article" data-event="rr-more">Amazon Kindle Users Are Getting the Washington <i>Post</i> for Free</a><a href="http://time.com/3578098/taylor-swift-spotify-ceo/" class="read-more-list-article" data-event="rr-more">Spotify CEO &#8216;Really Frustrated&#8217; With Taylor Swift</a><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/michael-brown-shooting/pair-suspected-trying-acquire-bombs-ferguson-protests-n254021?cid=par-time_20141122" class="read-more-partner-article" data-event="rr-partner" target="_blank">Feds Suspect Pair Sought Bombs for Ferguson Protests <span>NBC News</span></a><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/news/crime-courts/ohio-men-wrongly-convicted-murder-after-39-years-released-n253356?cid=par-time_20141122" class="read-more-partner-article" data-event="rr-partner" target="_blank">Two Ohio Men Wrongly Convicted of Murder Walk Free <span>NBC News</span></a><a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/fsu-shooter-myron-may-left-message-i-do-not-want-n253436?cid=par-time_20141122" class="read-more-partner-article" data-event="rr-partner" target="_blank">FSU Shooter Left Message: 'I Do Not Want to Die in Vain' <span>NBC News</span></a></div></aside><p>Aereo worked by giving each of its subscribers access to a tiny antenna that picked up broadcast television signals, which were then stored in a cloud server before being beamed over the Internet to users&#8217; laptops or mobile devices, either almost live or well after-the-fact via DVR technology. Subscribers paid about $8 a month for the service, even though broadcasters like NBC and Fox give away their content for free to anyone with an antenna in range of their transmitters, making most of their profits from advertising.</p>
<p>But advertising isn&#8217;t the broadcasters&#8217; only revenue stream. Cable companies like Time Warner Cable have for years been legally required to pay broadcasters for the right to retransmit their content to cable subscribers. What sparked the Aereo case is that Aereo didn&#8217;t pay those fees, which make up an increasingly large slice of the broadcasters&#8217; revenues. So broadcast networks, including CBS, NBC, ABC and Fox, sued Aereo on copyright grounds. The case ultimately found its way to the Supreme Court, which in June <a href="http://time.com/2921020/supreme-court-rules-tv-streaming-startup-aereo-is-illegal/" target="_blank">sided against</a> Aereo. Aereo then tried a few legal hail-marys to try saving its business, but as prime Aereo backer Barry Diller <a href="http://time.com/2921376/aereo-barry-diller/" target="_blank">admitted</a> over the summer, the game was over once the Court&#8217;s gavel was struck.</p><div class="content-ad" id="content-ad-3599505"></div>
<p>What I have trouble moving past is that Aereo wasn&#8217;t really charging for <em>content, </em>as everything you could watch on the service was free anyway. It was charging for <em>convenience &mdash; </em>You could watch Aereo on a laptop or iPhone, and it gave customers access to a cloud-based DVR to store their favorite shows. It also made up for the fact that, here in building-packed New York City at least, the free, over-the-air broadcasts are often difficult to watch with a regular TV aerial. Most of the people I know who used Aereo here did so because they couldn&#8217;t get reliable signals from the broadcasters. In this sense, Aereo addressed a technical failure, too. With those factors combined, Aereo was certainly worth eight bucks a month.</p>
<p>The broadcast networks used the courts to pummel Aereo into submission, suing a potential industry disruptor out of existence. But instead of walking away smiling, those broadcasters should realize Aereo only foreshadowed a massive industry shakeup that will change everything about television. As more people cut the cord and switch to on-demand services like Netflix and HBO Go (with the latter soon to be available without a cable subscription), cable television will slowly die out &mdash; and take those lucrative retransmission fees with them as it goes. CBS, at least, sees the writing on the door: It&#8217;s <a href="http://time.com/3513843/hbo-cbs-streaming/" target="_blank">launching</a> an innovative subscription-based online service, from which it&#8217;ll likely make money off ads, too. More broadcasters should realize that cable TV is the past, not the future. And what better, bolder move to make than buying Aereo?</p><aside class="right-rail-module rr-ad" data-name="rr-ad"><div class="right-rail-ad" id="right-rail-ad-3599505"></div></aside><aside class="right-rail-module rr-share" data-name="rr-share"><span class="social-links">
    <a class="time-icons time-icons-mail social-link-mail" href="mailto:?subject=A%20TV%20Network%20Should%20Buy%20Aereo.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why.%20%7C%20TIME&body=A%20TV%20Network%20Should%20Buy%20Aereo.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20Why.%0A%0AIt%20would%20help%20them%20compete%20against%20Netflix%20and%20HBO%20Go%0A%0Ahttp%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F" data-event="email" title="Click to Email this article"></a>
    <a class="time-icons time-icons-fb social-link-fb popup" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F" data-event="fb-share" title="Click to post this article to Facebook"></a>
    <a class="time-icons time-icons-tw social-link-tw popup" href="#" data-href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwp.me%2Fp5HMd-f6ox&text=Why%20a%20TV%20network%20should%20buy%20Aereo&via=TIMEBusiness" data-event="tweet" title="Click to Tweet this article"></a>
    <a class="time-icons time-icons-linkedin social-link-linkedin popup" href="http://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=http%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F3599505%2Faereo-bankruptcy%2F&title=A+TV+Network+Should+Buy+Aereo.+Here%E2%80%99s+Why." data-event="linkedin" title="Click to post this article to LinkedIn"></a>
